recordedby: K.L. Ilves, M.W. Westneat, C.C. Baldwin, A.M. Quattrini, R.I. Eytan, G.W. Chaplin
samplingprotocol: rotenone: 2 12 x 18 bags of rotenone slurry, each composed of: 1 kg 5% powdered rotenone (Chem Sect brand from TIFA International) mixed with half a bottle of phosphate-free dish detergent (Joy Ultra-Concentrated) and seawater; spear
locality: Andros Island, Green Cay, shallow patch reef (AGC1)
locationremarks: Across Tongue of the Ocean to Green Cay; travel time to site from Andros Diving (Kemps Bay): ~80 min; Not historical Bohlke & Chaplin site - that site was sand in a few feet of water; site chosen to be comparable to patch reefs sampled at Andros & New Providence Islands; patch reef in ~ 20 ft; dive 1: rotenone dispersed along sand and western edge of patch reef; good kill but too many grunts; diverse coral patch but much of the coral dead; dive 2: Ilves, Quattrini, Eytan - habitat survey; boat crew (Reel Tight Charters): Captain Roggie and 1st mate Steve
identificationremarks: tissue sample: tags B2350, B2351 (2 of 2 tagged); tissues preserved in RNAlater, stored at -20C
dataset_citation: Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia. ANSP Ichthyology. Source: http://phylo.ansp.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=ansp_ich (source published on 2015-08-31)

recordedby: K.L. Ilves, M.W. Westneat, C.C. Baldwin, A.M. Quattrini, R.I. Eytan, G.W. Chaplin
samplingprotocol: rotenone: 2 12 x 18 bags of rotenone slurry, each composed of: 1 kg 5% powdered rotenone (Chem Sect brand from TIFA International) mixed with half a bottle of phosphate-free dish detergent (Joy Ultra-Concentrated) and seawater
locationremarks: Travel time from Driggs Hill Marina: 20 min; Tidal creek, south shore of Southern Bight, near E end - Historical Bohlke & Chaplin site; rotenone laid out at 12:46pm at high tide; Ilves on SCUBA starting at western most point at rock-mangrove interface moving east and north; rotenone laid along rock wall and bottom around entire rocky region with up to 15 ft depth; Eytan & Chaplin laid rotenone along the mangrove region starting at the NE corner moving south; tide rushed out very quickly aided by wind; much rotenone probably washed out; generally poor kill; boat crew (Reel Tight Charters): Captain Steve & 1st mate Darren
identificationremarks: tissue sample: tags B2559, B2560, B2561 (3 of 3 tagged); tissues preserved in RNAlater, stored at -20C; specimen B2561 juvenile

bibliographiccitation: Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia. ANSP Ichthyology. Record ID: urn:lod.ansp.org/catalog:ANSP:FISH:ANSP199433_A222F206-55DB-402B-B4AA-1EC53663A3CB_2015-5-14. Source: http://phylo.ansp.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=ansp_ich (source published on 2015-08-31)
recordedby: K.L. Ilves, M.W. Westneat, A.M. Quattrini, R.I. Eytan, G.W. Chaplin
samplingprotocol: rotenone: 2 12 x 18 bags of rotenone slurry, each composed of: 1 kg 5% powdered rotenone (Chem Sect brand from TIFA International) mixed with half a bottle of phosphate-free dish detergent (Joy Ultra-Concentrated) and seawater; spear
locationremarks: travel time to site from Andros Diving (Kemps Bay): 45 min; arrived at site with tide coming in, just before slack tide; patch reef surrounded by Thalassia beds in sand; dive 1: dispersed rotenon at SE corner of reef at slack tide, took > 10 minutes for rotenone to have effect; good kill; dive 2: incredibly strong current; Ilves, Quattrini, Eytan - habitat survey; Westneat - spearing; Chaplin - picking up additional rotenone-affected fishes; boat crew (Reel Tight Charters): Captain Roggie and 1st mate Steve  - they hooked barracuda
identificationremarks: tissue sample: tags B2075, B2076 (2 of 2 tagged); tissues preserved in RNAlater, stored at -20C
dataset_citation: Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia. ANSP Ichthyology. Source: http://phylo.ansp.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=ansp_ich (source published on 2015-08-31)

bibliographiccitation: Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia. ANSP Ichthyology. Record ID: urn:lod.ansp.org/catalog:ANSP:FISH:ANSP199436_25B6F5B1-5E25-4160-91A5-CDC7D7E5DD80_2015-5-14. Source: http://phylo.ansp.org:8080/ipt/resource.do?r=ansp_ich (source published on 2015-08-31)
recordedby: K.L. Ilves, M.W. Westneat, C.C. Baldwin, A.M. Quattrini, R.I. Eytan, G.W. Chaplin
samplingprotocol: rotenone: 2 12 x 18 bags of rotenone slurry, each composed of: 1 kg 5% powdered rotenone (Chem Sect brand from TIFA International) mixed with half a bottle of phosphate-free dish detergent (Joy Ultra-Concentrated) and seawater; spear
locality: Andros Island, Mastic Cay, historical site (MCH)
locationremarks: travel time from Driggs Hill Marina: 60 min; windy (~20 knots) & choppy, tide coming in; site a circular coral formation with large hole ~ 12-15' deep, top of reef ~3' deep; dive 1: rotenone laid out by Ilves & Eytan along perimeter of crevice, slightly under ledge; wind & waves carried fish northwards; Baldwin on snorkel, others on SCUBA; good kill but too many squirrelfishes, dozens likely left on reef; dive 2: Ilves & Quattrini habitat survey; boat crew (Reel Tight Charters): Captain Steve & 1st mate Darren
